Nigerians are brushing up on the men's beard boom. That's as the male grooming business booms globally. Courtesy #DStv403 ABUJA - Nigerians are brushing up on the men's beard boom. Men with well-kept facial hair are a growing trend and there's brisk business to help them stay in shape. At a barbershop in Abuja, men spend as much time having their beards done, as they do their hair. READ: Metrosexual grooming becoming more popular The male styling industry, on the whole, is experiencing a boom. Young modern males place increasing emphasis on their appearance and with Africa's growing young population the market is only going to get bigger. Watch the video above for more details.